    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-11-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="543" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">The Secretary of State</persName> to
                                    <persName type="to">Clarence A. Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,
                                            Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-11-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 1, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I transmit herewith, for your
                                information, a copy of a letter addressed by me, to-day, to Señor
                                Matias Romero, the envoy extraordinary and minister plenipotentiary
                                of the Mexican republic, which relates to the formation of the
                                Mexican Express Company, recently organized in the city of New York,
                                and with which you appear to be connected.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clarence</hi> A. <hi rend="smallcaps">Seward,</hi> Esq., New York.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
